<TEXT>
a retired general services administration 
official faces a maximum 36year prison term when hes sentenced 
feb 3 for receiving 24185 in bribes to provide inside information 
to two businessmen who were found guilty of conspiracy 
lester h finotti jr 56 a former manager in gsas 
transportation audit branch was convicted by a us district court 
jury of receiving the money and the use of a luxury automobile 
during an 18month period ending in september 1986 
william h white sr 59 and carmine w depietro 53 the former 
president and former executive vice president respectively of 
southern investment co were convicted of conspiracy to defraud the 
government 
the charge carries a fiveyear term 
the three defendants were allowed to remain free on bond until 
their sentencing feb 3 by us district judge harold greene 
the scheme involved an effort to obtain inside information from 
gsa to help the fayetteville nc company which purchased 
billsoflading at a discount from moving companies that hauled 
furniture of government employees 
under the arrangement known as factoring the moving companies in 
effect paid southern investment a premium to receive their money 
faster than if they waited for the government to pay them directly 
southern investment in turn assumed total liability for any 
claims for damaged freight that the government filed against the 
trucking companies 
the prosecution presented evidence that finotti provided 
information about the reliability of freight haulers that enabled 
white and depietro to decide whether to factor a companys 
billsoflading 
such information would enable southern investment to avoid 
purchasing moving bills from companies that would likely incur large 
damage claims the prosecution contended 
the indictment charged that finotti manipulated the payment of 
billsoflading to benefit southern investment 
finotti of waldorf md was convicted of conspiracy bribery 
conflictofinterest and filing a false government financial 
disclosure statement that did not report his financial arrangement 
with southern investment co 
</TEXT>
