<TEXT>
fire raced through the attic of a downtown 
motel late friday night leaving guests homeless causing minor 
injuries to three people and gutting the top floor of the twostory 
building officials said 
the fire was reported at 1130 pm fire chief don werner said 
werner said he didnt know how many guests were evacuated from the 
village inn motel but said the fire gutted at least 26 rooms 
a woman who jumped from a secondstory balcony was treated for a 
minor ankle injury and smoke inhalation and two people were treated 
for smoke inhalation said a paramedic who refused to give his name 
a number of people lost belongings to the blaze werner said 
the fire began in a corner of the ushaped motel and moved 
through the attic around the building 
all the rooms on the top floor suffered heavy fire damage and 
most of the room beneath sustained water and smoke damage officials 
said 
about 60 columbus firefighters responded to the blaze which sent 
smoke over several blocks of the citys old german village 
neighborhood 
residents of a nearby apartment complex were evacuated as a 
precaution because of the smoke werner said 
