to shanghai and areas of the southern provinces of guangdong and 
fujian where it had previously been eliminated 
snail fever also known as schistosomiasis is prevalent in 12 
provinces and is most serious in riverside or swampy areas of 
hubei jiangxi anhui and jiangsu provinces 
the disease transmitted into the bloodstream by a parasite 
results in fever distended stomach rashes inflammation of the 
liver and in severe cases death china says it has cured more than 
11 million sufferers or 95 percent of all victims of the disease 
since 1949 
