the oathtaking on the west front of the capitol overlooking the 
city and the mall will be a solemn contrast to four days full of 
official and unofficial parties pageants balls receptions galas 
salutes celebrations and festivals 
stephen studdert director of the presidential inaugural 
committee has said the bush inauguration will feature more free 
activities than ever before a sketchy schedule released last week 
shows at least three major events for children and youth including 
a festival entitled george to george two hundred years 
some of the capitals best known landmarks will once again be the 
sites of inaugural balls including the national air and space 
museum the kennedy center and the grandly restored union station 
the inaugural planners goal of broad participation is in keeping 
with the open relaxed style of george and barbara bush but there 
will be glamour aplenty what with nine balls and innumerable other 
upscale events 
roll call the weekly capitol hill newspaper published a special 
inauguration preview section suggesting 10 places to throw your 
inaugural party and noting that for inaugural week a limo can 
be a must the newspaper also canvassed fashion experts at local 
department stores and concluded that inaugural dress this year will 
run to ultraformal sophisticated classics 
capital area hotels are pulling out all the stops for 
inauguration week guests with special menus patriotic decorations 
and individual perks including chocolate elephant lollipops white 
chocolate replicas of the white house and sixinch square chocolate 
pianos filled with sweets 
its a grand piano the lid is up the truffles and goodies are 
inside the piano where the strings would be explained park hyatt 
spokeswoman jan walker you can eat the whole blooming piano 
officials at the presidential inaugural committee declined to 
discuss how much money they hope to raise to pay for the 
festivities the price tag could be higher than ever before since a 
new law requires the committee to reimburse the pentagon for its 
expenses in helping plan staff and execute inaugural activities 
president reagans 1985 inauguration committee raised more than 
12 million to pay for its events but a congressional study found 
that the use of federal employees cost taxpayers another 155 
million 
the pentagon alone spent 10 million and used 8400 military 
personnel who served as chauffeurs and escorts musicians and 
coatcheckers photographers and even organizers of receiving lines 
the two exceptions to the reimbursement rule are the inaugural 
ceremony and a lunch for the president vice president and 
congressional leaders both traditionally organized by the joint 
congressional committee on inaugural ceremonies 
the committee will distribute 70000 inaugural tickets to 
congress 40000 to republicans and another 30000 to the press 
governors diplomats and other customary guests 
if ifs too cold to have it outside the guest list goes from 
140000 to approximately 950 the amount that will fit inside the 
capitol rotunda said congressional committee director mike 
ruehling he said preparations for an indoor ceremony will be made 
in advance which guarantees that it wont happen 
while reagan took his first oath outside the capitol in balmy 
55degree weather a record high for inauguration day his second 
inaugural ceremony was forced indoors due to a record low 
temperature of 7 degrees the parade was canceled to the 
disappointment of hundreds of thousands of prospective spectators 
and young marching band members 
there was one inaugural week parade in 1985 a rainbow coalition 
march down pennsylvania avenue led by jesse jackson a twotime 
contender for the democratic presidential nomination 
jackson capped the march by blasting reagan for taking from the 
poor and giving to the rich and characterized the inaugural 
goingson as vulgar expressions of ostentatiousness private 
airplanes and long limousines and 25000 dresses and diamonds from 
south africa 
this year the mood is somewhat different jackson lunched with 
bush at the white house last week and came away smiling im 
impressed with the vice presidents openness he said whatever 
i can do in some role i would 
