support facilities for its naval operations in the waterway 
the arrangements are a particularly sensitive matter in oman 
which shares control of the strategic strait of hormuz with iran and 
has the closest ties of any gulf arab state with tehran 
the omanis permit the us navy to refuel warships at a base on 
the arabian sea and have access to other facilities that us 
officials refuse to discuss 
