weapons and led by col mohamed ali seineldin 54 remained in 
control of an infantry school 
loyal troops who fired several volleys of mortar shells at the 
rebels on friday surrounded the school supported by at least 16 
medium tanks and armored personnel carriers 
although the army provided no figures on the number of troops 
present witnesses said loyal troops surrounding the infantry school 
and in the base area appeared to number between 3000 and 4000 
the army said in a communique that four military men were wounded 
in exchanges of fire friday including a first lieutenant who was 
listed in critical condition a captain and two noncommissioned 
officers the army did not say to which band they belonged 
earlier news agencies had reported that the first lieutenant was 
killed 
local press reports indicated friday night that a 19yearold 
woman walking on the base was wounded by gunfire 
vice president victor martinez announced friday night that the 
uprising had been overcome but spokesmen for the rebels quickly 
disputed that claim early saturday 
roman catholic priest luis jardin who claimed to be a personal 
friend of seineldin left the infantry school early saturday and 
was quoted by the private news agency noticias argentinas as saying 
that a truce of several days had been agreed on by the rebels 
and caridi 
seineldin has not surrendered nor does he intend to said 
jardin 
seineldin a combat veteran of the 1982 falkland islands war with 
britain told reporters friday he and his men did not want to 
overturn the government but sought to restore military honor to 
the army and review the trials that punish the just and promote the 
guilty 
a radio station in the northern province of corrientes claimed to 
have obtained a proclamation from rebel supporters which spelled out 
demands 
the rebels radio provincia de corrientes said seek replacement 
of the current general staff and an immediate end to trials of 
military men accused of human rights abuses in a 1970s war against 
leftist subversives at least 9000 argentines disappeared 
during that time and are presumed dead 
the station also said the rebels sought special budget treatment 
for the armed forces army spending has been drastically slashed by 
a government plagued by deficit spending tripledigit annual 
inflation and a 56 billion foreign debt 
