the final word on fruitcake is out 
in time for christmas after a fiveyear battle that reached the 
highest echelon of german justice 
in a decision handed down friday by the supreme court the 
distinction of dresden fruitcake was determined to be its 
content not the location of the ovens that produce it 
the case stemmed from a bakerys complaint that a competitor was 
misleading customers by calling its product dresden fruitcake 
dresden is a city in east germany famous for producing the 
popular fruit and nut cake 
a lower court ruled the dresden name was a geographic designation 
and therefore misused when applied to baked goods produced elsewhere 
the high court overturned that decision saying the label had 
been used for years by bakers outside the dresden area and that west 
germans knew the cake was not produced in dresden 
