customers most analysts agree they have by no means solved the 
problem of restoring confidence in the market 
on the contrary they have raised fears of new shocks when the 
superstructure of debt created by the buyouts is sooner or later 
tested in a business downturn 
in the long term i think its unhealthy for the markets 
said joseph hardiman president of the national association of 
securities dealers which supervises the overthecounter market 
scandals over insider trading and other abuses also still cloud 
the outlook 
there is the matter of industry image or reputation or 
integrity call it what you will said edward obrien president 
of the securities industry association it is undeniable that it 
has been tarnished in the past few years 
while obrien argued that some criticisms of wall streets 
behavior have gone beyond what is justified he also acknowledged 
that they have stung 
in my view there is no magic potion that can be taken to 
produce a happy new world and national media campaigns are not the 
answer he said 
then too there is the question of whether investigations and 
reform measures since the 1987 market collapse have done enough to 
restore faith in the mechanism of the marketplace itself 
arthur levitt jr chairman of the american stock exchange 
thinks not he urged that the new administration and congress 
appoint a commission to do a longterm study of the markets 
more than 13 months after the fact he said i dont think 
anyone understands last october 
those who hold out hope for revived enthusiasm in the near future 
say their conviction lies in the very caution and pessimism that are 
so prevalent now 
they point to measures of investment advisory sentiment that have 
lately turned as gloomy as at any time since just before the start 
of the 198287 bull market 
and indeed adherents of this school of contrary opinion made 
their presence felt in the past weeks trading activity 
the dow jones industrial average of 30 industrials rose 1760 to 
209228 
the new york stock exchange composite index gained 239 to 
15302 the nasdaq composite index for the overthecounter market 
added 753 to 37391 and the amex market value index was up 408 to 
29527 
volume on the big board averaged 13254 million shares a day 
against 10786 million the previous week 
with so much money stockpiled in cds and money market 
investments a drop in interest rates might well give stocks a big 
lift said john bachmann a st louis brokerage executive who was 
chairman of the securities industry association the past two years 
in the crash he said the public was bruised and frightened 
but not broken i suspect we could have a surprisingly good year in 
